[3] Kyrgyzstan
Date: Fri 10 Jun 2011
Source: KABAR [edited]
http://eng.kabar.kg/index.php?option=com_content&showall=1&task=category&id=8Â§ionid=1&cid=2608&Itemid=1


83 cases of measles have been registered in Kyrgyzstan as of 9 Jun
2011 according to the press service of the Ministry of Health. A total
of 66 of the cases have been registered in Osh oblast, 16 in Bishkek
and one in Naryn oblast.

Specialists on immunization intend to appeal to WHO representation in
Kyrgyzstan with the suggestion to initiate measles vaccination of
children at 6 or 9 months of age, the reason being that infants are
now more often appearing among those affected.

